---
import ToolLayout from '../../layouts/ToolLayout.astro';
import NutritionCalculator from '../../components/calculators/NutritionCalculator.astro';
---

<ToolLayout
  title="Nutrition Planning Tools"
  description="Complete nutrition planning tools designed for men over 40. Calculate your protein needs, macro distribution, and optimal meal timing based on your specific goals and schedule."
>
  <div class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none mb-8">
    <h2>Why Proper Nutrition is Critical After 40</h2>
    <p>
      As men age, particularly after 40, nutritional needs change significantly. Hormonal changes, decreased muscle mass,
      and slower recovery rates make proper nutrition even more crucial for maintaining health and achieving fitness goals.
    </p>
    
    <div class="my-6">
      <h3>Key Nutritional Considerations for Men Over 40</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Protein Needs:</strong> Increased protein requirements to combat age-related muscle loss</li>
        <li><strong>Metabolic Changes:</strong> Typically requiring fewer calories but more nutrient-dense foods</li>
        <li><strong>Recovery Nutrition:</strong> Strategic nutrient timing to support longer recovery periods</li>
        <li><strong>Hormone Support:</strong> Proper fat intake for optimal testosterone production</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <NutritionCalculator />

  <div class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none mt-8">
    <div class="my-6 p-4 bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg">
      <h3 class="mt-0">Understanding Your Results</h3>
      
      <h4>Protein Recommendations</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Minimum: Essential for maintaining muscle mass</li>
        <li>Optimal: Supports muscle growth and recovery</li>
        <li>Distribution: Spread across 4-5 meals for better utilization</li>
      </ul>

      <h4>Macro Distribution</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Protein: Higher needs for muscle preservation</li>
        <li>Carbs: Adjusted based on activity level and goals</li>
        <li>Fats: Essential for hormone production</li>
      </ul>

      <h4>Meal Timing</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Pre-workout: Fuel for performance</li>
        <li>Post-workout: Optimal recovery window</li>
        <li>Throughout day: Sustained energy and protein synthesis</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h2>Implementing Your Nutrition Plan</h2>

    <h3>Protein Sources Guide</h3>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div>
        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Complete Proteins</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Lean meats (chicken, turkey)</li>
          <li>Fish (salmon, tuna)</li>
          <li>Eggs</li>
          <li>Greek yogurt</li>
          <li>Whey protein supplements</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Plant-Based Options</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Quinoa</li>
          <li>Legumes + rice</li>
          <li>Soy products</li>
          <li>Hemp seeds</li>
          <li>Pea protein supplements</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3>Quality Carbohydrate Sources</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Sweet potatoes</li>
      <li>Brown rice</li>
      <li>Quinoa</li>
      <li>Oats</li>
      <li>Fruits (especially berries)</li>
      <li>Vegetables</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Healthy Fat Sources</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Avocados</li>
      <li>Nuts and seeds</li>
      <li>Olive oil</li>
      <li>Fatty fish</li>
      <li>Eggs</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-900 p-4 rounded-lg mt-6">
      <h3 class="text-blue-900 dark:text-blue-100 mt-0">Pro Tips for Success</h3>
      <ul class="text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-200">
        <li>Prep meals in advance to ensure consistent nutrition</li>
        <li>Keep protein-rich snacks readily available</li>
        <li>Track your food intake for the first few weeks</li>
        <li>Adjust portions based on hunger and energy levels</li>
        <li>Stay hydrated - aim for 0.5-1oz per pound of body weight</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-6">
      <h3>Supplement Considerations</h3>
      <p>
        While whole foods should be your primary source of nutrition, certain supplements can be beneficial for men over 40:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Protein Powder:</strong> Convenient for meeting increased protein needs</li>
        <li><strong>Creatine Monohydrate:</strong> Supports muscle strength and recovery</li>
        <li><strong>Vitamin D3:</strong> Essential for testosterone production and bone health</li>
        <li><strong>Fish Oil:</strong> Supports joint health and reduces inflammation</li>
        <li><strong>Magnesium:</strong> Aids in recovery and sleep quality</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</ToolLayout>
